% if: executable(zoxide)

Zq - Quickly jump to a directory

$ [prgm]zq[/prgm] [arg-value]dot[/arg-value]  # Open fzf, pre-populated with zoxide query results

[prgm]zoxide[/prgm] (aliased to the [prgm]z[/prgm] command) makes it easy to jump to commonly used directories. If it jumps to the wrong directory, run [prgm]z[/prgm] [arg-value]dirname[/arg-value] again to jump to the next most likely directory.

Alternatively, use the [prgm]zq[/prgm] function to narrow down the list until a single result is left.

For even faster access, use [bold]Alt + Z[/bold] to open [prgm]zq[/prgm]
